Ancient Tombs Found in East China
JINAN , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- Chinese archeologists have discovered two ancient tombs dating back to the Yuan ( 1271 - 1368 ) and Ming ( 1368 - 1644 ) dynasties in the city of Heze in Shandong Province .
Zhou Fuyuan , director of the Heze City Museum , said that an abundance of relics including porcelain pots , bronze mirrors and funereal artifacts have been found .
A dozen stone sculptures featuring humans as well as animals such as sheep , tigers , and horses , which were typical commemorative figures erected in front of ancient tombs , are among the treasures , Zhou said .
The discovery will provide valuable insights for archeological research on the folk customs of the two dynasties , he added .
